                diagram, Approach to action I and II — the case of a foreign executive branch.
                    I. The new user has found that the relevant executive branch (here that of F team)
                      lies outside the tree of his chosen executive system.  It is foreign.  Either it
                      belongs to another system, or it floats independent of any.  The appointment offer
                      connecting it to the system (dashed line to F team) lies open.
                        : cf. `^^diagram, Approach to action I — finding where to engage`
                    II. The new user wishes to coordinate his actions with the members of that branch.
                      At the same time, he wishes to retain the context of his chosen executive system,
                      way model and endmost goal.  To do this, he pipes not from the model of the branch
                      as ordinarily he would (that of F team), but from the model of the native
                      appointing officer (that of B2 division).
