                diagram, How an executive officer finds candidate foreign branches for a way part
                  in need of execution.  The officer and his integrator:
                    1) Indentify in the way model the relevant, executable files of the way part.
                       For each file:
                    2) Indentify in the way-file forest the compatible files, e.g. integrable with the
                       way model.  From among all files both relevant and compatible (both 1 and 2):
                    3) Choose the most suitable executive branch, focusing e.g. on those with the most
                       appointment offers, applicants and members.
                  Represented are: 1) the way model of the executive officer and his integrator
                  (here those of B2 division); 2) cross linkage from each file of the model
                  to its way-file forest; and 3) cross linkage from each file of the way-file forest
                  to the leaf branches of the executive forest that deal with that file, shorn of any
                  (e.g. of integrative branches) known to be irrelevant to the search.
                  Model ‘MB2’ and branch ‘F team’ are those of the same labels in the preceding diagram.
